label.value: normal rate of actomyosin contractile ring assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of actomyosin contractile ring assembly is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Contractile ring assembly is the part of cytokinesis in which the actomyosin contractile ring is formed of actin, myosin, and associated proteins.

label.value: decreased rate of protein exchange in actomyosin contractile ring

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of protein exchange in the actomyosin contractile ring is decreased. Normally, proteins including actin and myosin are turned over between the contractile ring and elsewhere in the cytoplasm; exchange is faster during than before ring constriction.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to actin cable

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to actin cables is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Actin cables are parallel actin filament bundles nucleated by formin, and are the most common form of actin filament bundles found in yeasts.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: long mitotic spindle during anaphase A

value.value: A spindle phenotype in which the mitotic spindle is longer than normal during anaphase A.

label.value: decreased protein localization to nucleus, with protein mislocalized to cytoplasm during mitosis

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus is decreased, and some of the protein is present in the cytoplasm instead, during mitosis.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal volume aseptate spheroid vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is shaped in the form of a spheroid, has no septum, and has a normal volume.

label.value: normal shmoo morphology

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which the size, shape, or structure of the mating projection is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: inviable after spore germination, single or double cell division, spherical cell with cell lysis

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce a cell that is spherical, and undergoes one or two rounds of cell division before all cells die, and some cells lyse.

label.value: decreased number of elongated microtubule bundles curved around cell end

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which all detectable microtubules are present in fewer bundles than normal (usually only one or two), and bundles are longer than normal and curved around one or both ends of the cell.

definition.value: Curved microtubules follow a smooth bend rather than a straight line. This phenotype is observed during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: short misoriented interphase microtubules

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells form cytoplasmic microtubules that are shorter than normal and have abnormal orientation. The normal orientation is parallel to the long axis of the cell.

label.value: inviable mononucleate vegetative cell, with normal cell length and increased cell diameter

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is inviable, has one nucleus, and has normal length but a greater diameter than normal.

label.value: inviable binucleate vegetative cell, with normal cell length and increased cell diameter

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is inviable, has two nuclei, and has normal length but a greater diameter than normal.

definition.value: When using this term, also consider annotating to a cell cycle arrest term, such as 'abnormal cell cycle arrest in mitotic telophase' (FYPO:0000622); 'abnormal cell cycle arrest in mitotic anaphase' (FYPO:0000619) may be applicable if the assay detects DNA masses. Binucleate cells often arise as a result of cell cycle arrest.

label.value: inviable stubby multinucleate vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetatively growing cell is inviable and has more than one nucleus, and the cell diameter is larger than normal and the cell length is shorter than normal.

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'inviable cell population' (FYPO:0002059) or one of its descendants.

label.value: sensitive to phosphate starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to phosphate starvation.

definition.value: Use this term if you have assayed growth of cells exposed to calcium starvation in culture. If you have assayed the response to calcium starvation at the subcellular or molecular level, consider annotating to 'abnormal cellular response to calcium starvation' (FYPO:0001200).

label.value: abnormal regulation of adenine biosynthetic process

value.value: A regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which regulation of an adenine biosynthetic process is abnormal.

label.value: normal RNA level during cellular response to hydroxyurea

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to hydroxyurea is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased cellular dATP level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of dATP measured in the cell is lower than normal.

label.value: normal cellular dCTP level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of dCTP measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal cellular dGTP level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of dGTP measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased protein localization to chromatin during cellular response to phosphate starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin is decreased during a cellular response to phosphate starvation.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased rate of actin filament depolymerization

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of actin filament depolymerization, i.e. the removal of actin monomers from a filament, is decreased.

label.value: altered RNA level during cellular response to copper ion starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell differs from normal during a cellular response to copper ion starvation. Total RNA or a specific RNA, such as the mRNA transcribed from a gene of interest, may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased RNA level during cellular response to copper ion starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to copper ion starvation is lower than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased RNA level during cellular response to copper ion starvation during spore germination

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to copper ion starvation is lower than normal during spore germination. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, before germ tube formation

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates but dies before forming a germ tube or dividing. Such spores exit dormancy and undergo isotropic swelling but the spore wall does not rupture and no germ tube emerges.

definition.value: Spores with this phenotype can be identified by loss of spore refractility that can be observed by light microscopy or by a decrease in optical absorbance of the spore suspension.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, before germ tube formation, during copper ion starvation

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates but dies before forming a germ tube or dividing, when spore germination takes place under conditions of copper ion starvation. Such spores exit dormancy and undergo isotropic swelling but the spore wall does not rupture and no germ tube emerges.

definition.value: Spores with this phenotype can be identified by loss of spore refractility that can be observed by light microscopy or by a decrease in optical absorbance of the spore suspension.

label.value: normal septum morphology

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the size, shape, and structure of the septum is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased spore germination frequency during copper ion starvation

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which the frequency of occurrence of spore germination is decreased when germination takes place under conditions of copper ion starvation.

definition.value: Note that this phenotype is usually assayed by observing a population of spores and observing how many germinate. Also consider annotating to 'inviable spore (FYPO:0002151)' with an extension to indicate incomplete penetrance, especially if you have a quantitative measurement.

label.value: actin cables present in decreased numbers

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells contain fewer actin cables than normal.

label.value: normal establishment of actomyosin contractile ring localization

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which establishment of actomyosin contractile ring localization is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Establishment of actomyosin contractile ring localization is the part of cytokinesis in which the actomyosin contractile ring is assembled in a specific location.

label.value: increased protein localization to nucleolar periphery

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the border of the nuclear and nucleolar regions is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: sensitive to potassium ion starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to potassium ion starvation.

definition.value: Use this term if you have assayed growth of cells exposed to potassium starvation in culture.

label.value: normal cell population growth during potassium ion starvation

value.value: A cell growth phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) under conditions of potassium ion starvation.

definition.value: Use this term if you have assayed growth of cells exposed to potassium starvation in culture.

label.value: abolished protein localization to septum

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cell septum does not occur.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to cell division site, with protein mislocalized to cytoplasm

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the site of cell division is decreased, and some of the protein is present in the cytoplasm instead.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased phosphatidylinositol phosphate level in plasma membrane

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of one or more phosphatidylinositol phosphates measured in the plasma membrane is higher than normal when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

definition.value: An increased level of a protein in the plasma membrane may result from increased protein transport to the membrane ('increased protein localization to plasma membrane FYPO:0002127), decreased endocytosis from the membrane ('abolished endocytosis' FYPO:0000421 or 'decreased endocytosis' FYPO:0000422), or both. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal ferrous iron import

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of ferrous iron ions into a cell is abnormal.

label.value: decreased ferrous iron import

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of ferrous iron ions into a cell occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: sensitive to tetramethylammonium

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to tetramethylammonium. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of tetramethylammonium that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: sensitive to spermidine

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to spermidine. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of spermidine that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: abnormal plasma membrane potential

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the plasma membrane potential, i.e. the electric potential existing across the plasma membrane, is abnormal.

label.value: increased plasma membrane potential

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the plasma membrane potential, i.e. the electric potential existing across the plasma membrane, is greater than normal.

label.value: increased duration of protein phosphorylation during cellular response to phosphate starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the duration of protein phosphorylation is longer than normal during a cellular response to phosphate starvation. All phosphorylation may be affected, or only phosphorylation of specific proteins, or even specific sites within specific proteins.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased cytoplasmic translational initiation during cellular response to oxidative stress

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of translational initiation in the cytoplasm is decreased during a cellular response to oxidative stress.

definition.value: Note that this term should be used only when an experiment measures the initiation of protein synthesis directly, e.g. by ribosome profiling. Consider annotating to 'decreased protein level' (FYPO:0000835) or one of its descendants.

label.value: decreased cytoplasmic translational initiation during cellular response to osmotic stress

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of translational initiation in the cytoplasm is decreased during a cellular response to osmotic stress.

definition.value: Note that this term should be used only when an experiment measures the initiation of protein synthesis directly, e.g. by ribosome profiling. Consider annotating to 'decreased protein level' (FYPO:0000835) or one of its descendants.

label.value: abolished protein phosphorylation during cellular response to hydrogen peroxide

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, does not occur during a cellular response to hydrogen peroxide.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to vacuolar membrane

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the vacuolar membrane is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased cell population growth on gluconate carbon source

value.value: A vegetative cell population growth phenotype in which cell growth is increased relative to normal in a medium containing gluconate as the carbon source.

definition.value: Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise.

label.value: normal level of macromolecular complex

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of any macromolecular complex present in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal cytosolic monomeric ribosome level

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells contain a normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) number of monomeric ribosomes (80S monosomes) in the cytosol.
